{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8359177c-3fb6-40c1-a822-057192a08351","content":"Your project uses MSTest 3.8.0 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP). The hang detection syntax differs from VSTest. For MTP, use:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m\n```\n\nHowever, since your `global.json` specifies MTP as the runner, the MTP-native equivalent is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nThe `--` separates `dotnet test` args from MTP-specific args. This will produce a hang dump if any test exceeds 5 minutes, helping you identify the culprit.\n\nWant me to run this for you now?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e3ec9b0b-8851-4479-b058-51cf3490a278","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is an MSTest 3.8.0 project using Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) runner, as indicated by the `global.json` setting `\"test\": { \"runner\": \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" }`. \n\nFor MTP, the hang detection is done differently than VSTest. With MTP, you use `--blame-hang-timeout` but the syntax might differ slightly. Let me check:\n\nFor VSTest: `dotnet test --blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5min`\nFor MTP: `dotnet test --blame-hang-timeout 5m` (or similar)\n\nActually, with MTP, the blame options are:\n\n\n- `--hangdump` to enable hang dump\n- `--hangdump-timeout` to specify timeout\n\nI need to verify the exact syntax for MTP's hang dump configuration since it differs from the standard VSTest blame options.","outputTokens":444,"requestId":"E3C4:207F19:537EDD:6072DF:6A052335"},"id":"dd383240-2905-418c-be23-4faa60ffebf9","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:20:00.440Z","parentId":"049739ef-b421-42b8-9359-86a83685b28d"}
